definitions.definition: Personification of fertile waters, she was a Titan daughter of Uranus and Gaia , and with her brother Oceanus gave birth to all rivers and the Oceanids .
A large ocean which formerly lay between Eurasia and Africa.

subdefinitions.definition: The iteration of this oceanic basin during the Mesozoic , the most recent iteration.

main_definition: ( Greek mythology ) Personification of fertile waters, she was a Titan daughter of Uranus and Gaia , and with her brother Oceanus gave birth to all rivers and the Oceanids .
secondary_definitions: ( geology ) A large ocean which formerly lay between Eurasia and Africa.
